Content: Dear Student, .Please do not reply to this email address. .Your tax invoice is attached. .If you have lodged a valid Commonwealth Assistance Form by the census date and are eligible for HECS-HELP or FEE-HELP or SA-HELP, your outstanding student contribution amount, tuition fees or student services and amenities fees will be deferred to your loan at census date. Administrative fees cannot be deferred. .To make a payment: .- Log in to HiQ site .- Go to the 'Manage your enrolment' tab .- Under the 'Fees and Payments' portlet, select 'Pay tuition fees and charges' .For more information on how to pay please refer to: .https://www.student.qut.edu.au/fees-and-finances/paying-fees/how-to-pay .Please ensure full payment is made by the Due Date to avoid penalties. .If you have any enquiries regarding your Tax Invoice, contact Student Fees and Compliance via the Ask a Question function in AskQUT https://ask.qut.edu.au or telephone 07 3138 2000. .Regards, .Student Fees and Compliance
Subject: QUT Student Tax Invoice

Content: Hi Harry, .Just to confirm. .You are booked in to attend an interview with Andy Mullally on: .Friday 12th January 2018, at 10:30hrs at the Queensland Museum, South Brisbane. .Please bring with you: .Some photo I.D. and whichever proof of identity documents you will need to provide as part of your Blue Card application (see Part E on below link to check I.D. options). .Once you arrive at the Museum, head to the Level 2 Cloakroom and register with the staff located there. .The interview is an informal discussion and should only take around 25-30 minutes. .The aim is for me to get to know you, gauge your experience and interests and sight/scan any required documentation. .Formal attire is not required as I understand a lot of applicants are attending interviews either on their way to or from college, university or work. .Once again, I sincerely thank you for both your time and your expression of interest in volunteering for the World Science Festival Brisbane 2018. .I look forward to meeting you then. .Kind Regards – Andy .http://www.worldsciencefestival.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/WSFB2018VolunteerBlueCardApplication2018.pdf .From: Tran Quang Huy [mailto:quanghuy.qut@gmail.com] .Sent: Wednesday, 13 December 2017 12:51 PM .To: Andy Mullally .Subject: Re: World Science Festival Brisbane 2018 - Volunteering - REMINDER .Hi Andy, I'm interested in Volunteering for the World Science Festival Brisbane 2018. But I'm currently in Viet Nam until 10/1/2018. Can I have an interview with you after 10/1/2018? Thank you so much. .On Wed, Dec 13, 2017 at 7:57 AM, Andy Mullally > wrote: .Dear Harry Tran, .If you are still interested in Volunteering for the World Science Festival Brisbane 2018, please follow Blue Card application information detailed in original email (below) and contact me as soon as possible to arrange an interview. .All prospective WSFB 2018 Volunteers must be interviewed before FRIDAY 19TH JANUARY 2018. .I am available for interviews at the Queensland Museum: .Mon-Fri, 09:30-15:30 (with the exception of Christmas break period: 25th Dec – 1st Jan). .Kind Regards - Andy .Andy Mullally .Volunteer Coordinator .World Science Festival Brisbane .[QMN] .PO Box 3300 | South Brisbane BC | Queensland 4101 | Australia .t. 3842 9243 | m. 0416 465 960 | andy.mullally@qm.qld.gov.au .[email-signature-template-FINAL_03][email-signature-template-FINAL_04][email-signature-template-FINAL_05][email-signature-template-FINAL_06][email-signature-template-FINAL_07][email-signature-template-FINAL_09] .[http://intranet.qm.qld.gov.au/general/procedures/images/WSFB_2018_EMAIL_BLOCK_2.jpg] .Dear ., .Thank you very much for your initial expression of interest in the role of World Science Festival Brisbane 2018 - Volunteer. .Last year’s festival was a big success and we expect this year’s to be bigger, better and busier. .None of it would be possible without the valuable role that festival volunteers play; from ushering, way-finding assistance, manning information desks, technical support tasks and a host of pre and post festival support roles. Volunteers are the public face of the festival and they truly hold the key to enabling the public to get the very best experience from their festival visit. .At present, I am in the process of selecting and recruiting volunteers from our database of applicants. .A mandatory criterion for you to be able to work at next year’s festival is the possession of, or the ability to obtain a valid* Blue Card. .(*To be valid, Blue Cards must not expire before the end date of the festival: Sun 25th March 2018 or later if you are interested in any Volunteer roles that may be available post-festival). .If you already have a Blue Card – fantastic! You’re ahead of the game. .Just reply to this email confirming you’re still interested in the role and I’ll book an interview date with you over the coming weeks. .No Blue Card? The festival will apply for one on your behalf (no charge): .Below is the link to the WSFB 2018 Volunteer Blue Card application form. .http://www.worldsciencefestival.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/WSFB2018VolunteerBlueCardApplication2018.pdf .Please complete all relevant fields electronically (leave signature blank), then save, attach (just the form, no supporting documentation required at this stage please) and return to me via email as soon as possible. .Blue Cards can take several weeks to process, so don’t hold off for too long, as the recruitment period is finite. .There is NO charge for this application (ignore Part G – Payment Options). .Once I have received this completed form, I will contact selected applicants to arrange an interview date/time. .This interview will take the form of a brief, informal 15-20 minute discussion, whereby I can assess applicants suitability for the role, ascertain any key strengths and experiences they have, and also, if necessary, sight and copy Blue Card proof of identity documents which you will need to bring along with you (see list on form – Part E). .Successful confirmation of applicants becoming WSFB 2018 Volunteers will be based both on the interview, and if required, the successful processing of any Blue Card applications. .I’m really looking forward to meeting you and hopefully getting you ready for involvement in what truly is an amazing, memorable and inspiring event. .Thank you for your patience during the recruitment stage and once again, thank you very much for your interest in the role. .Kind Regards – Andy .Andy Mullally .Volunteer Coordinator .World Science Festival Brisbane .[QMN] .PO Box 3300 | South Brisbane BC | Queensland 4101 | Australia .t. 3842 9243 | m. 0416 465 960 | andy.mullally@qm.qld.gov.au .[email-signature-template-FINAL_03][email-signature-template-FINAL_04][email-signature-template-FINAL_05][email-signature-template-FINAL_06][email-signature-template-FINAL_07][email-signature-template-FINAL_09] .[http://intranet.qm.qld.gov.au/general/procedures/images/WSFB_2018_EMAIL_BLOCK_2.jpg]
Subject: RE: World Science Festival Brisbane 2018 - Volunteering - REMINDER

Content: [cid:image001.jpg@01D41844.6AE089D0] .Semester Two Events .Young Alumni @ River City Labs .QUT Young Alumni presents 'Not Just Another Networking Event' featuring QUT alumni, podcaster and Youtuber Hayley Angell. College of Excellence is sponsoring 10 students to attend this event. .5:30-9pm, Thursday 19 July .River City Labs .Secure your ticket via Careerhub. .Networking and Etiquette Workshop .Build your networking and etiquette skills to help you make the most of social opportunities to build your professional connections. .9-11am, Wednesday 25 July .S620, Gardens Point .Book in via Careerhub. .College of Excellence Welcome Event .The College of Excellence is hosting its biannual Welcome Event for new and existing members to socialise and hear of what's to come in the College for Semester two. .6-9pm, Thursday 26 July .OJW Room, Gardens Point .Book in via Careerhub. .Adulting 101 .For many of us, university has been the first exposure to the adult world. This workshop will provide you with essential Adulting information on Real Estate, Financial Planning and Contributing to Your City. .6-9pm, Monday 30 July .Gibson Room, Gardens Point .Book in via Careerhub. .Golden Key QUTxGriffith Focus on Technology Networking Event .Golden Key is inviting QUT College of Excellence and Griffiths Honour College members along to a panel discussion and networking event surrounding a focus on technology. .6:30-9:30pm, Tuesday 31 July .Little Tokyo Two .Find out more and book in here. .The Xcellence Factor .Have you got a knack for juggling, or the ability to make bird noises? Perhaps you have a cat that can jump through hoops? Or are you just really good at singing? If so, we encourage to take part in the CoE Xcellence Factor 2018! .5-10pm, Wednesday 8 August .F Block Amphitheatre, Kelvin Grove .Register your act via Careerhub .Book in via Facebook or Careerhub. .Career Management Skills .In an ever-changing and competitive job market, seeking employment can be a difficult and sometimes discouraging task. The College of Excellence will be hosting a workshop on the vital skills when trying to nail that interview or to write a curriculum vitae that stands out amongst the rest. .1-3pm, Thursday 9 August .B301, Kelvin Grove .Book in via Careerhub. .Dragon Boat Regatta Team - Last chance to register .Join the College of Excellence Dragon Boat Regatta Team! .Training dates are as follows: .Saturday 14 July .Sunday 29 July .Sunday 5 August .The event will be held on Saturday 11 August. .Find out more and register for the team here. .Telling Your Story .Whether in an interview, pitching an idea or product or presenting a persuasive speech, a speaker needs to convince their audience that they are credible; they need to share their experience, their passion and their story. This workshop will provide you with some verbal, vocal and visual strategies to create audience engagement and memorability through the medium of personal storytelling. .9am-1pm, Friday 24 August .V310, Gardens Point .Book in via Careerhub. .Life in the Real World .What do you want to know about life after graduation? We invite you to join us in hearing from CoE Alumni on their experiences since graduating. .Five CoE Alumni will share details of their diverse experiences, which include getting paid to travel the world, contributing to their community and field, returning to study and quitting their dream job. .Presentations will be followed by refreshments and networking. .6-8pm, Thursday 30 August .The Atrium, Level 6, P Block, Gardens Point .Book in via Careerhub. .Visit the College of Excellence Careerhub Website for more opportunities and email Karlee at collegeofexcellence@qut.edu.au with any questions, comments or concerns.
Subject: Semester Two Events

Content: Hi Harry, .I'm pleased to say your application was successful and you have been .invited to an interview (the suspense is over!). Please book a time .below for next week: .https://calendly.com/brittany-62/interview-for-work-experience/10-02-2018 .You don't need to bring anything in or print anything. The interview .is about getting to know your personality and to ensure you are a good .fit for the work. .Thanks, .Brittany Bennett .Marketing .brittany@codeheroes.com.au .www.codeheroes.com.au .0490 349 488 .On Tue, Sep 25, 2018 at 8:43 PM Tran Quang Huy .wrote: .> .> Hi Brittany, .> .> I have already attached my resume below. .> Hope to hear from you soon. .> .> Regards, .> Harry. .> .> On Tue, Sep 25, 2018 at 9:00 AM Brittany Bennett .wrote: .>> .>> Hi Harry, .>> .>> There are no specific requirements however a high GPA and good .>> attitude always help! Just need to send in your resume :) .>> .>> Brittany Bennett .>> Marketing .>> brittany@codeheroes.com.au .>> www.codeheroes.com.au .>> 0490 349 488 .>> .>> .>> On Mon, Sep 24, 2018 at 10:36 PM Tran Quang Huy .wrote: .>> > .>> > Hi, .>> > First of all, thank you for sending the invitation to me. .>> > About the work experience role, are there any specific requirements for the applicants related to the project? .>> > Hope to hear from you soon. .>> > .>> > Regards, .>> > Harry .>> > .>> > .>> > On Mon, Sep 24, 2018 at 12:18 PM Brittany Bennett .wrote: .>> >> .>> >> Hi, .>> >> .>> >> Brittany from Code Heroes here, we met a few months ago at the QUT .>> >> careers fair and you signed up as interested in our work experience .>> >> program. .>> >> .>> >> We have just opened up a position for work experience for an upcoming .>> >> project we are starting in a few weeks. We will be starting interviews asap. .>> >> .>> >> Thanks, .>> >> .>> >> .>> >> Brittany Bennett .>> >> Marketing .>> >> brittany@codeheroes.com.au .>> >> www.codeheroes.com.au .>> >> 0490 349 488

Content: View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/22bcdbab93cb/vncr-christmas-school-announcement-lessons-and-discussions-thng-bo-link-hc-tp?e=f51aa9ce70) .** Thông báo về tài liệu học tập và nơi thảo luận cho các bài học VNCR Christmas School .------------------------------------------------------------ .Chào bạn, .Cảm ơn bạn đăng ký tham gia khóa học mùa đông của nhóm Vietnamese Control and Robotics Group. Chúng tôi xin gửi bạn thông tin khóa học dưới đây. .+ Bài học: .Các bài học được đưa lên mạng ở địa chỉ sau: .https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=128092d1da&e=f51aa9ce70 .Các cập nhật về khóa học được đăng ở trang Facebook sau: .https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=7dc13c1636&e=f51aa9ce70 .(trang Facebook này cũng là nơi tiếp nhận các trao đổi chung về khóa học) .+ Thảo luận cụ thể cho từng bài học: .Người học và giảng viên trao đổi về từng bài học bằng cách gửi bài vào trang "padlet" riêng cho bài học. Trang padlet đóng vai trò như bảng đen (blackboard) online, người dùng có thể post nội dung mà không cần phải tạo tài khoản ở trang web đó. .Các giảng viên sẽ tham gia trao đổi trong thời gian khóa học (cho đến ngày 6/1/2019). Sau thời gian này, tài liệu về bài học và nơi thảo luận vẫn sẽ được để lại trên internet cho mọi người xem, nhưng các giảng viên sẽ không tham gia thảo luận ở đó nữa. .Robot motion planning 101: https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=28da9099de&e=f51aa9ce70 .C/C++ code generation for Matlab/Simulink: https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=ef32049757&e=f51aa9ce70 .Human factor: https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=f445f8457b&e=f51aa9ce70 .Introduction to PMSMs control: https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=703a8bcba7&e=f51aa9ce70 .Introduction to trajectory optimization: https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=74963f6dab&e=f51aa9ce70 .Tính toán đạo hàm & Giải bài toán MPC bằng Casadi: https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=eb735288ab&e=f51aa9ce70 .Giới thiệu về Python Numpy & Julia: https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=5b1a6cac43&e=f51aa9ce70 .Math’s in the AIR: https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=69f9c4e76d&e=f51aa9ce70 .Xin lưu ý là ở khóa học này, chúng tôi đưa các bài học theo chuyên môn riêng của từng người, và không kịp có thời gian để tổ chức các bài học cho có tính liên kết thông suốt. Cho nên, các bài học ít liên quan đến nhau, mỗi bài học có thể xem như để giới thiệu một lĩnh vực nghiên cứu riêng, các bạn có thể chọn học theo từng bài mà mình quan tâm. .Chúc các bạn nhiều thành công! .Nhóm giảng viên VNCR Christmas School .============================================================ .** (https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=72f19198ed&e=f51aa9ce70) .** (https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=59edf76a8c&e=f51aa9ce70) .** (https://google.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=d55cec07f5&e=f51aa9ce70) .Copyright © 2018 VNCR, All rights reserved. .You are receiving this email because you opted in via our website. .Our mailing address is: .VNCR .131B Nguyen Van Cu .Can Tho, Can Tho 900000 .Vietnam .Want to change how you receive these emails? .You can ** update your preferences (https://google.us7.list-manage.com/profile?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=14a304e29b&e=f51aa9ce70) .or ** unsubscribe from this list (https://google.us7.list-manage.com/unsubscribe?u=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&id=14a304e29b&e=f51aa9ce70&c=da0918ab14) .. .Email Marketing Powered by Mailchimp .http://www.mailchimp.com/monkey-rewards/?utm_source=freemium_newsletter&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=monkey_rewards&aid=51ba397af214514743c9f8579&afl=1
Subject: [VNCR Christmas School] Announcement - lessons and discussions (thông báo link học tập)

Content: Dear Quang Huy, .Thank you for your confirmation. I am pleased to advise that your place for the QUT OZ EX program has been successfully confirmed. .The event schedule of the OZ EX program is listed below for your information. .* .OZ EX Preparation Seminar: Friday 21 June 2019 .* .OZ EX Industry Project: Monday 24 June - Friday 28 June 2019 .* .OZ EX Showcase: Wednesday 3 July 2019 .The upcoming event, OZ EX Preparation Seminar will take place on 21 June, 2019. This seminar will provide detailed information about the program and prepare all participants for the Australian industry projects in the following week. .Below are the details of the OZ EX Preparation Seminar: .Date: Friday 21 June 2019 .Time: 1:30pm - 4:30pm .Location The Gibson Room (Level 10, Z Block, GP) .Please note that this event is compulsory for all participants. .We will continue to provide you information through emails when there is an update of the program. If you have any questions, you can contact the QUT OZ EX team at any time (ozex@qut.edu.au). We look forward to welcoming you soon. .Regards, .The QUT OZ EX Team .Queensland University of Technology (QUT) | 2 George St, Brisbane QLD 4000 | GPO Box 2434, Brisbane QLD 4001 .QUT OZ EX Website: www.qut.edu.au/events/oz-ex | Email : ozex@qut.edu.au | CRICOS No. 00213J .Connect with us: Instagram @qutinternational | Read our International student blog | Enquire to study .[cid:image001.png@01D50005.5B8C5E60]
Subject: QUT OZ EX - Participant Confirmation

Content: Dear students, .Welcome to the QUT Oz-Ex program! .Readygrad have partnered with QUT to provide this program to you. .You have been assigned to work on the "Virtual Digital Worker" project at 4Impact. .Please find attached your project brief. .Each project team has been assigned a leader, who will be responsible for any communication required to Readygrad on behalf of the group. .The purpose of your project placement is to develop experience working on real-life problems in a workplace setting. You will work with a mentor from your host company, who will brief you on the project and provide support throughout its completion. .Please see below for the project schedule: .Friday 21st June .Orientation Seminar .The seminar will be at QUT. Your university has provided details to you .Monday 24th June .First Day and Project Briefing .You and your group will attend your host company and receive a full brief for your project. Please arrive at the address indicated in your brief by 9am. On arrival, you can ask for your mentor, whose name is also listed in the brief .Monday 24th June - Friday 28th June .Project Work .You will work on your project throughout the week, both remotely and on-site .Wednesday 3rd July .Oz-Ex Showcase .You will be issued a certificate of participation, and have the opportunity to network with the host companies involved in the project .If you have any questions, please let me know. .Kind regards, .Emily .Emily Stannard .Education Partnerships Account Manager .Mobile:+61 (0)431 577 238 .Email:Emily.Stannard@readygrad.com.au .readygrad.com.au .Sydney .| .Melbourne .| .Adelaide .| .Perth .| .Brisbane .This email message may contain information that is confidential and subject to privilege. If you are not the intended recipient, you are notified that any use, dissemination, distribution or copying of this message is prohibited. If you have received this email in error, please notify us immediately and delete all material pertaining to this email. Gradability, Performance Education and Readygrad, are registered trading names of Gradability Pty Ltd (ABN 86 117 850 281) RTO number 91436. The views expressed in this message are those of the individual sender, except where the sender specifically states that they are the views of Gradability Pty Ltd or its associated entities. Gradability Pty Ltd is not a registered migration agency. No employees of Gradability Pty Ltd are qualified to provide migration advice. Please ensure that all migration advice is obtained from a registered migration agent.
Subject: QUT Oz-Ex Program Project Brief

Content: Hi Quang Huy, .Apologise for previous incorrect information about your project. Your correct project is with 4Impact, in Group 1. .Please let me know if you have further questions. .Kind regards. .Ruby Law | International Engagement Officer | QUT International .Ph: +61 (7) 3138 1863 | .Email: ozex@qut.edu.au .Queensland University of Technology (QUT) | 2 George St, Brisbane QLD 4000 | GPO Box 2434, Brisbane QLD 4001 .QUT OZ EX Website: www.qut.edu.au/events/oz-ex | Email : ozex@qut.edu.au | CRICOS No. 00213J .Connect with us: Instagram @qutinternational | Read our International student blog | Enquire to study .[cid:image001.png@01D5276A.2A5D6C80] .From: QUT OZ EX .Sent: Thursday, 20 June 2019 11:12 AM .To: quanghuy.qut@gmail.com .Subject: REMINDER: OZ EX Preparation Seminar .Dear Quang Huy, .This is a friendly reminder that the QUT OZ EX program is commencing shortly. The preparation seminar will be held this Friday at 1:30pm in the Gibson Room located on level 10, of Z block. Please review the agenda for the complete QUT OZ EX program below: .Date .Event .Location .Friday 21st June .1:30pm - 4:30pm .(Please arrive 15 minutes earlier to meet your team) .Preparation Seminar .The Gibson Room .Level 10, Z Block, GP campus .Monday 24th June .Project Briefing .Mummy's Wish .Monday 24th June - Friday 28th June .(40 hours, Business hours apply) .Project Work .Mummy's Wish .Wednesday 3rd July .1:15pm - 4:45pm .OZ EX Showcase .The OJW Room, .Level 12, S Block, GP Campus .As part of the QUT OZ EX program you are required to complete the following program tasks with your assigned group, led by the team leader, and guided by your industry mentor: .1. .Project .You have been assigned in Group 10, with Mummy's Wish. Please refer to the full details of the project brief sent by ReadyGrad. A copy of the project brief will also be provided to you at the Preparation Seminar. .2. .Communication Task .Alongside the project brief, your team has been assigned a communication task to reflect on your QUT industry project experience. This task is designed to showcase your teams QUT OZ EX experience and can be used as a tool for future reflection. Your team is required to create an Instagram account, and post images of your experience daily. This task will be coordinated by your team's communications officer and Full details will be provided at the Preparation Seminar. .If you have any questions, you can contact the QUT OZ EX team at any time (ozex@qut.edu.au). We look forward to seeing you on Friday at the Preparation Seminar. .Regards, .The QUT OZ EX Team .Queensland University of Technology (QUT) | 2 George St, Brisbane QLD 4000 | GPO Box 2434, Brisbane QLD 4001 .QUT OZ EX Website: www.qut.edu.au/events/oz-ex | Email : ozex@qut.edu.au | CRICOS No. 00213J .Connect with us: Instagram @qutinternational | Read our International student blog | Enquire to study .[cid:image004.png@01D5276A.1CA8F870]
Subject: RE: REMINDER: OZ EX Preparation Seminar
